**Trace:** Template structure derived from procedures/synthesis.md Steps 1-6 output requirements. Section ordering follows procedure step order to allow partial-completion checkpointing (grouped table and contradiction log written before confidence map, per Step 2 checkpoint rule). Counter-prior section (Step 3.6) positioned before principles section (Step 3.7) to force counter-hypothesis generation before conclusions are locked in. Each section has instructional comments explaining what to fill in and what constitutes an incomplete entry (e.g., blank contradiction section with no "no contradictions found" statement). Observable-violation conditions from CLAUDE.md domain failure modes are embedded as comments in the relevant sections. Round 1 correctness audit fixes (2026-07-04): changed counter-prior observable violation from ≥2 to ≥1; removed Step 5 "that requires a design decision" qualifier; added Action column clarifying comment distinguishing status-tracking text from result text. Round 1 completeness audit fixes: added CONTESTED and GAP variant blocks to Step 3.7 section; added Step 5 empty-state instruction; added repeated-pattern format example; added skeleton timing instruction (Expected tier first, Actual tier last); fixed footer to handle both scale-gate states; added Step 4 implicit assumption row format. All Round 2 audits GREEN (2026-07-04). Phase 7 cross-file audit fixes (2026-07-04): added "empirical" to pre-specified threshold statement (previously omitted — inconsistent with synthesis.md Step 3 formal definition and CLAUDE.md); strengthened counter-prior observable violation from "empty section" to "count of entries fewer than count of HIGH groups" to catch partial-coverage failures.
